/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 54 738 Tm
13 TL
() Tj
T*
(Whisper is useful when the user speaks in real-world conditions that are not perfectly clean. It is a strong fit for community screening environments where recording quality can vary.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**How the project uses it**) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The repo includes Whisper as an alternative speech family alongside wav2vec2. It can be fine-tuned for Bengali and Hindi speech and selected through the voice training pipeline.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 3.3 Audio Pipeline Functionality) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The audio workflow typically follows this sequence:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. A voice clip is uploaded or captured.) Tj
T*
(2. The selected ASR model converts speech to text.) Tj
T*
(3. The transcript is passed into the text screening logic.) Tj
T*
(4. The system can also attach modality quality metadata to show whether audio was usable, partial, or weak.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This design keeps the system flexible. Even when a voice model is not available, the assessment can still proceed through text and questionnaire inputs.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 4. Vision and Image Models) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.1 MediaPipe Face Mesh) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**What it is**) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(MediaPipe Face Mesh is a landmark detection system for faces. It predicts dense facial keypoints rather than only detecting the face bounding box.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Working principle**) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- The image is normalized and passed through the facial landmark detector.) Tj
T*
(- The model returns facial mesh coordinates.) Tj
T*
(- Those coordinates can be turned into derived measurements such as facial geometry, eye openness, and other visual signals.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Why it matters in this project**) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The system uses image inputs as one more modality for screening support. Face landmark extraction helps build lightweight visual features without needing a heavyweight custom image classifier for every case.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**How the project uses it**) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The feature extraction path uses MediaPipe Face Mesh in static image mode when available. The implementation reports the backend as mediapipe_face_mesh when that route succeeds.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### 4.2 OpenCV Haar Fallback) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**What it is**) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
11 0 obj
<< /Type /Page /Parent 16 0 R /MediaBox [0 0 612 792] /Resources << /Font << /F1 1 0 R >> >> /Contents 10 0 R >>
