1 0 0 1 54 738 Tm
13 TL
(OpenCV Haar cascades are classical computer-vision detectors, not deep learning models.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**Why it is included**) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The project uses Haar-based face detection as a fallback when the primary face mesh pipeline cannot run. This improves robustness in low-dependency or partially configured environments.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**How the project uses it**) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(If the face mesh route is unavailable, the system can still detect or crop a face region using Haar-based detection so that downstream processing is not blocked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 5. Supporting Data Sources) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(These are not models, but they matter because they shape how the models learn:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- **MELD**: used for proxy text supervision and emotion-aligned language patterns.) Tj
T*
(- **RAVDESS**: used for proxy audio and image supervision.) Tj
T*
(- **DAIC-WOZ**: used as the clinical supervision source for more realistic depression-oriented training and evaluation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(These datasets help the project bridge the gap between broad representation learning and clinically relevant screening behavior.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 6. Downstream Screening Heads) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The repository also contains downstream trained bundles that sit on top of the deep learning feature extractors.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Important note:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- these downstream bundles are not themselves deep learning models) Tj
T*
(- they are usually classical estimators or lightweight classifier heads) Tj
T*
(- they consume embeddings, transcript features, and modality summaries) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The project now uses the stronger bundles as the first choice for each modality:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- text_transformer before classical text) Tj
T*
(- audio before the auxiliary audio branches) Tj
T*
(- image_dl before classical image) Tj
T*
(- comorbidity after the improved upstream modality outputs have been stabilized) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(In other words, the deep learning models do the representation learning, and the screening heads do the final risk estimation and aggregation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 7. Multimodal Decision Flow) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The final assessment is built from several signals:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- questionnaire scores) Tj
ET
endstream
