(- text embeddings and safety signals) Tj
T*
(- audio transcript or audio-derived features) Tj
T*
(- image-derived facial signals) Tj
T*
(- modality quality and confidence indicators) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This multimodal design is important because mental health screening in the field is rarely supported by one perfect input. The system therefore combines multiple weak-to-moderate signals into one practical screening outcome.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 8. Practical Behavior in the App) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The app does not depend on every model being available at runtime.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(If a transformer or speech checkpoint is not installed locally, the application:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- falls back to lighter heuristic logic) Tj
T*
(- keeps the assessment flow working) Tj
T*
(- preserves saved records and reports) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This means the project is robust enough for development machines, demo environments, and partially configured deployments.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 9. Research and Paper Writing Notes) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(When you describe this system in a paper, it is useful to separate the model families by function:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- **Text understanding**: BERT, DistilBERT, MuRIL, IndicBERT) Tj
T*
(- **Speech understanding**: wav2vec2, Whisper) Tj
T*
(- **Vision landmarks**: MediaPipe Face Mesh) Tj
T*
(- **Fallback vision support**: OpenCV Haar cascades) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(That separation makes the methodology section clearer and avoids mixing representation-learning models with downstream decision heads.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 10. Recommended Citation Targets) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For academic writing, this document should be paired with the references already present in paper/references.bib, especially for:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- MuRIL) Tj
T*
(- RAVDESS) Tj
T*
(- PHQ-9 and PHQ-4) Tj
T*
(- any clinical screening references already cited in the manuscript) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(If you add more model families later, extend this guide so the methodology section stays synchronized with the implementation.) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
